<p>Monday 5 March</p>
<p>Marched off to Edgehill &ndash; between Dernancourt and Buire &ndash; and witnessed the burial of Lt. Col. Williams.  A party of about 26 from our unit attended.  Bob Troup the batman who left Aust. with Lt. Col. Williams fainted at the graveside &amp; Capt. Irvine &amp; Major Donald were deeply affected.<br/>Pierrot Show in Albert after tea.</p>
